<h3>Web Designer</h3>

<p>Learning current best practices to design websites and web applications is an ever-changing journey of research, testing, failing, and discovery.</p>

<p>I started learning web design in 2005. At the time CSS was a new thing. I studied the <a href="http://www.csszengarden.com/">CSS Zen Garden</a> and many tutorials.</p>

<p>I like learning new skills and methods. I continued to learn web design during the introduction of HTML5 and CSS3 and JavaScript. I learned mobile-first responsive design. I learned SASS and how to build WordPress websites from scratch.</p>

<p>I strive to make my code be well written. I want to write semantic, assessable code. Just like making art or writing, the big Idea is what I reach for with web design. I want to create websites that attract viewers.</p>

